RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 81. Starter Allowance Purse 9500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $3,500 OR LESS SINCE JUNE 3, 2022 AND WHICH HAVE NOT WON A STARTER ALLOWANCE RACE AT EMERALD DOWNS IN 2023. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden Races, Claiming Races And Starters Races For $3,200 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHESAHEATWAVE stalked the early paced, moved up along the outside to join Red Panty Raid nearing the five-eighths pole, dueled with that one from and and prevailed in a prolonged drive. RED PANTY NIGHT hopped in the air at the start, then moved up to open a clear early lead, responded when challenged nearing the five-eighths pole and disputed the issue to the wire but wasn't quite good enough in a game effort. DANCE LADY saved ground stalking the pace, angled out nearing the three-sixteenths pole but was unable to reach the top two in a steady effort. NOUMEA saved ground while being unhurried and failed to threaten. SASSY EINSTEIN was allowed to settle in stride while racing three-wide and failed to be a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Noumea
ENTRY.OWNER: James Carter R and Soranno Jillian

ENTRY.NAME: Shesaheatwave
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked, vied final 5/8, prevailed, prolonged drive

ENTRY.NAME: Red Panty Night
ENTRY.COMMENT: hopped start, cleared early, dueled, game effort

RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 2 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 9000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TYCHE AWAITS YOU vied the early lead while three-wide, dueled with Let It Reign throughout and proved best in a stiff drive. LET IT REIGN vied for the lead from along the inside, wasn't quite good enough but held on gamely to the wire. DONTFORGETHESUGAR was allowed to settle in stride early, moved up along the inside on the turn, angled out nearing the three-sixteenths pole and finished strongly. CALYPSO PRINCESS stumbled at the start then was reserved off the pace, moved up four-wide nearing the quarter pole, was bumped by Drinkup Buttercup and finished willingly when clear. DRINKUP BUTTERCUP vied for the early lead from between horses, began dropping back after a quarter mile, came out to bump Calypso Princess leaving the quarter pole and tired.

ENTRY.COMMENT: settled, inside move turn, angled out 3/16, strong finish

ENTRY.NAME: Drinkup Buttercup
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied early, 2-wide, drifted out 1/4, bumped, tired

ENTRY.NAME: Tyche Awaits You
ENTRY.OWNER: Crowe Shelly M and Richards Jay

RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 3 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 76. Maiden Claiming Purse 10000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 121 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000, if for $7,000, allowed 3 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TENNESSEE MOON saved ground setting the pace racing in hand and drew off to win as much the best. PISTA GIRL was bumped hard by Zeva Dee shortly after the start, then bobbled to drop far behind the field, rallied five-wide the final quarter mile and finished strongly. ZEVA DEE broke out sharply to bump with Pista Girl, then saved ground chasing the leader, slipped through during the drive and finished in a mild rally. OUR GIRL ASHLEY dropped back early, came three-wide into the stretch and passed tiring rivals. MISCHIEF MAME prompted the issue from along the outside to the stretch and tired. A STORM TOO SOON was forwardly placed for three furlongs racing along the inside and gave way.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 4 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 68. Maiden Claiming Purse 16500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 121 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: METEOR SHOWER stalked the pace racing in hand, rallied two-wide into the stretch and finished fast to be up in the final strides. SENSIBLE LUTE saved ground setting the pace, settled into the stretch with a clear lead and just failed to last. STARRY BEACH was allowed to settle in stride while three-wide on the turn, angled in during the drive and closed strongly. SHORT JOURNEY hopped slightly at the start, then saved ground while being unhurried, was in tight from the three-eighths pole to the quarter pole, angled out and finished willingly when clear. A LITTLE GRACE was reserved off the the pace while racing slightly off the rail and lacked a rally. SPARKLES AND SPURS dropped back early, raced three-wide on the turn and failed to threaten.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 5 1M Dirt CR: 88. Claiming Purse 9500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE DECEMBER 3, 2022 OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE MARCH 3, 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $3,500 (Claiming Races For $3 ,200 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: UNCLE JEFF vied with MARKSMAN ON TARGET for the lead racing in hand, shook that one off nearing the quarter pole, repulsed a bid from COMMAND SGT MAJOR entering the stretch and quickly drew clear. COMMAND SGT MAJOR was reserved off the early pace, moved up three-wide nearing the quarter pole but was unable to stay with the winner during the drive while proving to be second best. SPIRE was unhurried early, moved up two-wide on the turn splitting rivals nearing the quarter pole and finished in a mild rally. MARKSMAN ON TARGET vied for the lead from along the inside for nearly six furlongs and tired. POPPY'S C NOTE dropped back early while saving ground and failed to menace. STREET DEMAND was allowed to settle in stride, raced three-wide approaching the quarter pole and gave way.

ENTRY.NAME: Poppy's C Note
ENTRY.COMMENT: dropped back, saved ground, no menace
